# AGENTS.md - Agent Rules (generated by @pukujan/context-engineering)

## State Management (Hard Rules)

**Source of truth:** `buildplan/agent_state.json` (machine-readable, agent writes here)
**Checksum:** `buildplan/agent_state.sha256` (auto-updated on every state change)
**View:** `MEMORY.md` (read-only for agent, generated from agent_state.json)

### Workflow
1. **Read `MEMORY.md` on session start** — restore project context
2. **Edit `buildplan/agent_state.json`** — update state as you work
3. **Regenerate `MEMORY.md`** — run `python3 scripts/render_memory.py`
4. **Archive session** — run `python3 scripts/measure_context.py --archive-session --slug <slug> --tokens <count>`

### Context Budget
- **Ceiling:** 30,000 tokens per session (warn-only — never aborts the agent)
- **Tracked by:** `scripts/measure_context.py`
- **Tracker:** `buildplan/context_budget.json`
- **Check status:** `python3 scripts/measure_context.py --status`
- **Start session:** `python3 scripts/measure_context.py --tokens 0 --start-session`

### Phase Gate (optional)
- Before transitioning work phases, run: `python3 scripts/check_gate.py --module <slug>`
- Runs `lint:architecture` only when the host project defines it

### Session Archives
- Location: `work-log/sessions/`
- Format: `{YYYY-MM-DD}-{slug}.md`
- Index: `work-log/sessions/INDEX.md`

## Memory Rules
- ~30k token ceiling with warn-only procedure (compact + archive, do not stop work)
- Session memory: read MEMORY.md on start, archive + prune on end
- Terse bullets, no prose
